<p><b>A/HRC/24/L.7 
</b></p>
<p><b>  24</b>/&#8230; <b> The rights to freedom of peaceful assembly and of association 
</b></p>
<p><b> 1. Sixth preambular paragraph 
</b></p>
<p>The paragraph <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p><i>Taking note</i> of the report of the Special Rapporteur on the rights to freedom of 
</p>
<p>peaceful assembly and of association submitted to the Human Rights Council at its twenty-
</p>
<p>third session,1 
</p>
<p><b> 2. Seventh preambular paragraph 
</b></p>
<p><i>Delete</i> the paragraph. 
</p>
<p><b> 3. Paragraph 2 
</b></p>
<p>The paragraph <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p>2. <i>Reminds</i> States of their obligation to respect and fully protect the rights of all 
</p>
<p>individuals to assemble peacefully and associate freely, online as well as offline, including 
</p>
<p>in the context of elections; 
</p>
